					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yes, &quot;it's so bad&quot; ... Still don't know that movie. (Shame on me)<br /><br />Thanks for the infos! On the c64, it is a 16k rom cartridge, but it is decompressed into 40k ram at startup, using prepack6502 and exomizer and some additional crazy tricks... On the NES, this is not possible, because of the lack of ram, so I would probably want to use a standard UxROM with 64k PRG rom. (8k CHR ram?)<br /><br />This audio IRQ split is clever, then no special mapper would be required.<br /><br />The bigger problem is that I didn't know that I can only access CHR ram in vblank. Meh, have to think about it. The cartridge should be as cheap as possible, so PRG ram is not a good option.</div>

